snippet: Federal regulators shut down the commercial fishing season for northern shrimp in the Gulf of Maine on Wednesday, citing concerns about the declining population and higher ocean temperatures.
abstract: Federal regulators shut down commercial fishing season for northern shrimp in Gulf of Maine for second straight year, citing concerns about the declining population and higher ocean temperatures.
lead_paragraph: Federal regulators shut down the commercial fishing season for northern shrimp in the Gulf of Maine on Wednesday, citing concerns about the declining population and higher ocean temperatures.
